modules.description: Provides functions to transliterate Unicode characters into ASCII equivalents, handling a wide range of scripts and special symbols. Works with strings and individual code points, offering precise control over the conversion process. Used to normalize user input for search indexing, generate URL slugs, or process international text in legacy systems.

Provides functions to determine the byte length of UTF8 characters and to decode them into ASCII equivalents. Works with strings and individual characters, handling both single-byte and multi-byte sequences. Translates non-ASCII characters like "À" to "A" or "Ч" to "TCH" and allows custom handling of unsupported characters.
